<div class="c330_15">
<div id="v330.15.1"><span class="H1697 s">And the word</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H559 s"> came unto me, saying</span>,</div>
<div id="v330.15.2"><span class="H1121 s">Son</span><span class="H120 s"> of man</span><span class="H1612 s">, What is the vine</span><span class="H6086 s"> tree</span><span class="H6086 s"> more than any tree</span><span class="H2156 s">, <i>or than</i> a branch</span><span class="H6086 s"> which is among the trees</span><span class="H3293 s"> of the forest</span>?</div>
<div id="v330.15.3"><span class="H6086 s">Shall wood</span><span class="H3947 s"> be taken</span><span class="H6213 s"> thereof to do</span><span class="H4399 s"> any work</span><span class="H3947 s">? or will <i>men</i> take</span><span class="H3489 s"> a pin</span><span class="H8518 s"> of it to hang</span><span class="H3627 s"> any vessel</span> thereon?</div>
<div id="v330.15.4"><span class="H5414 s">Behold, it is cast</span><span class="H784 s"> into the fire</span><span class="H402 s"> for fuel</span><span class="H784 s">; the fire</span><span class="H398 s"> devoureth</span><span class="H8147 s"> both</span><span class="H7098 s"> the ends</span><span class="H8432 s"> of it, and the midst</span><span class="H2787 s"> of it is burned</span><span class="H6743 s">. Is it meet</span><span class="H4399 s"> for <i>any</i> work</span>? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Is it…: Heb. Will it prosper?)</span></div>
<div id="v330.15.5"><span class="H8549 s">Behold, when it was whole</span><span class="H6213 s">, it was meet</span><span class="H4399 s"> for no work</span><span class="H6213 s">: how much less shall it be meet</span><span class="H4399 s"> yet for <i>any</i> work</span><span class="H784 s">, when the fire</span><span class="H398 s"> hath devoured</span><span class="H2787 s"> it, and it is burned</span>? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (meet: Heb. made fit)</span></div>
<div id="v330.15.6"><span class="H559 s">Therefore thus saith</span><span class="H136 s"> the Lord</span><span class="H3069 s"> GOD</span><span class="H1612 s">; As the vine</span><span class="H6086 s"> tree</span><span class="H6086 s"> among the trees</span><span class="H3293 s"> of the forest</span><span class="H5414 s">, which I have given</span><span class="H784 s"> to the fire</span><span class="H402 s"> for fuel</span><span class="H5414 s">, so will I give</span><span class="H3427 s"> the inhabitants</span><span class="H3389 s"> of Jerusalem</span>.</div>
<div id="v330.15.7"><span class="H5414 s">And I will set</span><span class="H6440 s"> my face</span><span class="H3318 s"> against them; they shall go out</span><span class="H784 s"> from <i>one</i> fire</span><span class="H784 s">, and <i>another</i> fire</span><span class="H398 s"> shall devour</span><span class="H3045 s"> them; and ye shall know</span><span class="H3068 s"> that I <i>am</i> the LORD</span><span class="H7760 s">, when I set</span><span class="H6440 s"> my face</span> against them.</div>
<div id="v330.15.8"><span class="H5414 s">And I will make</span><span class="H776 s"> the land</span><span class="H8077 s"> desolate</span><span class="H4603 s">, because they have committed</span><span class="H4604 s"> a trespass</span><span class="H5002 s">, saith</span><span class="H136 s"> the Lord</span><span class="H3069 s"> GOD</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (committed…: Heb. trespassed a trespass)</span></div></div>
